#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.37:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.37:0.2"
msgid "4. devatāvagga "
msgstr "4. Deities "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Chaḷaṅgadānasutta "
msgstr "37. A Gift With Six Factors "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.336, sc1
msgctxt "an6.37:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Not sure why BB uses perfect here, the tense is the same as the next sentence.
msgctxt "an6.37:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena veḷukaṇḍakī nandamātā upāsikā sāriputtamoggallānappamukhe bhikkhusaṃghe chaḷaṅgasamannāgataṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpeti. "
msgstr "Now at that time Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother, was preparing a religious donation for the mendicant Saṅgha headed by Sāriputta and Moggallāna. "

msgctxt "an6.37:1.3"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena veḷukaṇḍakiṃ nandamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ sāriputtamoggallānappamukhe bhikkhusaṃghe chaḷaṅgasamannāgataṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpentiṃ. "
msgstr "The Buddha saw her doing this, with his clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, "

msgctxt "an6.37:1.4"
msgid "Disvā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "and he addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.37:1.5"
msgid "“esā, bhikkhave, veḷukaṇḍakī nandamātā upāsikā sāriputtamoggallānappamukhe bhikkhusaṃghe chaḷaṅgasamannāgataṃ dakkhiṇaṃ patiṭṭhāpeti. "
msgstr "“This Veḷukaṇṭakī, Nanda’s mother, is preparing a religious donation for the mendicant Saṅgha headed by Sāriputta and Moggallāna. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an6.37:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, chaḷaṅgasamannāgatā dakkhiṇā hoti? "
msgstr "And how does a religious donation have six factors? "

msgctxt "an6.37:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni honti, paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni. "
msgstr "Three factors apply to the donor and three to the recipients. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.37:2.3"
msgid "Katamāni dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni? "
msgstr "What three factors apply to the donor? "

# NOTE: The nuance in the terms for positive emotions here is interesting. sumana is a more general sense of well-being, good mood. Pasada comes in the act of doing. While attamana is the result of something. I render the latter more literally, sometimes it just means “pleased”, but it usually refers to an uplifting emotion that results from something positive.
msgctxt "an6.37:2.4"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako pubbeva dānā sumano hoti, dadaṃ cittaṃ pasādeti, datvā attamano hoti. "
msgstr "It’s when a donor is in a good mood before giving, while giving they feel confident, and after giving they’re uplifted. "

msgctxt "an6.37:2.5"
msgid "Imāni dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni. "
msgstr "These three factors apply to the donor. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an6.37:3.1"
msgid "Katamāni paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni? "
msgstr "What three factors apply to the recipients? "

msgctxt "an6.37:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, paṭiggāhakā vītarāgā vā honti rāgavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītadosā vā honti dosavinayāya vā paṭipannā, vītamohā vā honti mohavinayāya vā paṭipannā. "
msgstr "It’s when the recipients are free of greed, hate, and delusion, or practicing to be free of them. "

msgctxt "an6.37:3.3"
msgid "Imāni paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni. "
msgstr "These three factors apply to the recipients. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.37:3.4"
msgid "Iti dāyakassa tīṇaṅgāni, paṭiggāhakānaṃ tīṇaṅgāni. "
msgstr "Thus three factors apply to the donor and three to the recipients. "

msgctxt "an6.37:3.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, chaḷaṅgasamannāgatā dakkhiṇā hoti. "
msgstr "That’s how a religious donation has six factors. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an6.37:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ chaḷaṅgasamannāgatāya, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇāya na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gahetuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s not easy to grasp the merit of such an offering by saying that "

msgctxt "an6.37:4.2"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattatī’ti. "
msgstr "this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that nurtures happiness and is conducive to heaven, ripening in happiness and leading to heaven. And it leads to what is likable, desirable, agreeable, to welfare and happiness. "

#. VAR: asaṅkhyeyyo → asaṅkheyyo (bj, s1-3, km) | asaṃkheyyo (pts1)
msgctxt "an6.37:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.337, sc5
msgctxt "an6.37:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāsamudde na sukaraṃ udakassa pamāṇaṃ gahetuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s like trying to grasp how much water is in the ocean. It’s not easy to say "

msgctxt "an6.37:5.2"
msgid "‘ettakāni udakāḷhakānīti vā ettakāni udakāḷhakasatānīti vā ettakāni udakāḷhakasahassānīti vā ettakāni udakāḷhakasatasahassānī’ti vā. "
msgstr "how many gallons, how many hundreds, thousands, hundreds of thousands of gallons there are. "

msgctxt "an6.37:5.3"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāudakakkhandhotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of water. "

msgctxt "an6.37:5.4"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, evaṃ chaḷaṅgasamannāgatāya dakkhiṇāya na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gahetuṃ: "
msgstr "In the same way, it’s not easy to grasp the merit of such an offering … "

msgctxt "an6.37:5.5"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro sovaggiko sukhavipāko saggasaṃvattaniko iṭṭhāya kantāya manāpāya hitāya sukhāya saṃvattatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an6.37:5.6"
msgid "Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhaṃ gacchatī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an6.37:6.1"
msgid "“Pubbeva dānā sumano, "
msgstr "A good mood before giving, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:6.2"
msgid "dadaṃ cittaṃ pasādaye; "
msgstr "confidence while giving, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:6.3"
msgid "Datvā attamano hoti, "
msgstr "feeling uplifted after giving: "

# NOTE: I feel the translation misses something if the obvious allusion to Brahmanical sacrifice is lost.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: yaññassa → puññassa (mr)
msgctxt "an6.37:6.4"
msgid "esā yaññassa sampadā. "
msgstr "this is the perfect sacrifice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
#. VAR: Vītarāgā → vītarāgo (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an6.37:7.1"
msgid "Vītarāgā vītadosā, "
msgstr "Free of greed, free of hate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:7.2"
msgid "vītamohā anāsavā; "
msgstr "free of delusion, undefiled; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:7.3"
msgid "Khettaṃ yaññassa sampannaṃ, "
msgstr "this is the field for the perfect sacrifice, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: brahmacārayo → brahmacārino (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an6.37:7.4"
msgid "saññatā brahmacārayo. "
msgstr "the disciplined spiritual practitioners. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an6.37:8.1"
msgid "Sayaṃ ācamayitvāna, "
msgstr "After rinsing, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:8.2"
msgid "datvā sakehi pāṇibhi; "
msgstr "you give with your own hands. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:8.3"
msgid "Attano parato ceso, "
msgstr "This sacrifice is very fruitful "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:8.4"
msgid "yañño hoti mahapphalo. "
msgstr "for both yourself and others. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an6.37:9.1"
msgid "Evaṃ yajitvā medhāvī, "
msgstr "When an intelligent, faithful person, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:9.2"
msgid "saddho muttena cetasā; "
msgstr "sacrifices like this, with a mind of letting go, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:9.3"
msgid "Abyāpajjaṃ sukhaṃ lokaṃ, "
msgstr "that astute one is reborn "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.37:9.4"
msgid "paṇḍito upapajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "in a happy, pleasing world.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.37:9.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
